headline: A Look at Citi’s Valuation Following $80 Billion Wealth Management Move With BlackRock
summary: Citigroup (NYSE:C) has just made headlines with the announcement that it is entrusting about $80 billion in global wealth client assets to BlackRock. This is not a routine tweak to their business; it is the largest initiative of its kind for Citigroup’s wealth management arm. With the launch expected in the fourth quarter, investors are watching closely. The collaboration aims to widen the menu of investment options and harness BlackRock’s expertise in portfolio construction and technology to...

headline: Klarna IPO Update: Don't Buy Now Or Later
summary: Klarna's IPO is unattractive; its $13-14B valuation is far too expensive. Despite revenue growth, Klarna remains unprofitable and faces intense competition.
